content: So much fun and entertaining

This is really a very satisfying game, the pixel art is good and the game is challenging just the way I like it. The high encounter rate doesn't bug me at all since it lengthen the gameplay. Highly recommended if your looking for a good JRPG game. Edit: After a long while, I realized that it's much more of an story-driven game rather than a rpg game. There's not much to do in towns, there's no rest or anything, just crafting and that's it! Pretty fun tho, just hope there's more content.
Interesting so far

Don't listen to the other review. Save your game under data. Negatives: The encounter rate IS tuned a bit high. This is probably to convince you to buy the no encounters purchase. Positives: The interface is excellent. It's a very fresh style and the speech bubbles are charming. Map travel is nice. You plan out the whole round at once in an encounter, which will likely be interesting later. Graphics are nice. Stars off because this game is short.
Not bad, but game can get overbearingly difficult after a few hours in..especially with enemies hitting upwards 125% of your hp. Expect Game Overs to ensue.
As expected from a Kemco RPG! Hit-Point really improved through the years.

This is the worst game ever ,you can't do anything ,not even look around all you do is fight ,fight,and more fight,nothing to tell you what to do.dont believe all these people that praise this game with 5 stars it's phony ratings.this is why I'm changing from a 5 to a 1 star
Great game so far!
Thank you for fixing the volcano. I am stuck in the Deo Shandela ruins! Not able to make it through the heavy winds. Was pretty fun up until this point though

Fun game, good art, music, story, and gameplay. Dear Kemco, I have a suggestion. The passive item finding style in this game is glorious. For example, searching for items that increase hp by 100, or crt rate, or exp gain, for the whole party... It was really smart to make that a part of the game, please consider doing it again in future games. Thank you Kemco for another fun game.
I can't get past the blizzard in the final dungeon. Not sure if i missed something
Great game love it good story and hope you will create something as good as this or better.
Great game so far, but I like to be able to buy and use magic and healing potions. The lack of buying equipment is different. Fun game though.
Good game, fair controls, kinda grindy but I like that. Great soundtrack too üëå
love this game
Fun game.
Nice RPG games. If you are RPG gamer you must at least try this.

Nicely done game! The story and its theme of greed as a good thing (sorta) is a nice take over the "gotta save the world" superhero. Characters are pretty cool, but the 3rd and 4th could have used more fleshing out. Having only 4 people, it was pretty cool being able to adapt a person from tank to healer to powerhouse as desired or needed. Music was good, and bosses had some challenges to them at times. Only thing i hate is the glitch for the volcano. Cannot enter the place for a side quest.
Nice.
Good game, must play this game if you like jrpg

A quest for crystals with quirky characters. Pretty simple combat but challenging at times. Find treasure that adds a small percentage to various stats automatically. Really a pretty fun game. Plus I like the idea of a party member able to learn monster's skills.
Liking what hit point coming out with these ƒèays, another nice and fun game, thank you for publishing and translating this kemco. :)
Another great game, not use to not buying items but it's a fun game!!!
Quite an entertaining little adventure story, game play is pretty easy to follow and the graphics are real good.
So far its an average game. High encounter rate make it aggravating to play. And there is no save , only autosave.
Great Game Keep It Up Y'All.
